iduals have been found in Corrientes province and in southern Brazil, eastern Paraguay, and southeastern Uruguay. It has been listed as a separate species, Sporophila zelichi, the Entre Ríos, white-collared, Zelich's, or Narosky's seedeater. Differences are that it has a wide white collar all the way around the neck; the back is chestnut, not grey; and the rufous of the belly is darker than the marsh seedeater's. However, its status has been controversial since its discovery; some have suggested that it is a color morph of the marsh seedeater or the chestnut seedeater, or a hybrid between the two. The few recorded songs are the same as those of the marsh seedeater. Accordingly, the American Ornithologists' Union's South American Classification Committee voted in 2008 to remove S. zelichi from their list, with two voters favoring the suggestion that it is a morph of the marsh seedeater. Following them, it is considered to belong to the marsh seedeater here. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical dry lowland grassland and subtropical or tropical seasonally wet or flooded lowland grassland. It is threatened by habitat loss. If S. zelichi is a separate species, it would be critically endangered. References \"Species factsheet: Sporophila palustris\". birdlife.org. BirdLife International. 2016. Retrieved 28 May 2025.", "shortSummary": "The marsh seedeater (Sporophila palustris) is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae. It is sexually dichromic, with the males sporting…", "locations": ["巴拉圭", "乌拉圭"], "threats": ["栖息地破坏", "农药污染"], "lat": -34.0, "lng": -64.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/ae/Sporophila_palustris.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-sporophila", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-sporophila-palustris", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-sporophila", "species": "taxonomy-species-sporophila-palustris"}, "expandable": true, "x": 119.44, "y": -292.72, "z": 545.89}], "links": [{"key": "bird-marsh-seedeater-f5c114d2__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-sporophila-palustris", "source": "bird-marsh-seedeater-f5c114d2", "target": "taxonomy-species-sporophila-palustris", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-sporophila-palustris__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-sporophila", "source": "taxonomy-species-sporophila-palustris", "target": "taxonomy-genus-sporophila", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Marsh seedeater 属于属 Sporophila。"}]}
